The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 A Matador that was trailing a victory procession of Anadi Shahoo, the CPM candidate from Vidyasagar, knocked down three kids, leaving one dead on the spot, on Thursday evening. Shahoo himself was on the Matador.

 he accident occurred around 8 pm at the intersection of Sagar Dutta Lane and Phears Lane, under Bowbazar police station. The injured kids were taken to Medical College and Hospital. They were in a critical state. Local residents set up a roadblock, prompting senior police officers to rush to the spot.

 Digambar Jana, 55, accidentally fell off a state bus on SP Mukherjee Road around 11.35 am on Wednesday. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he died after battling for life for four hours. Jana was a resident of Thakurpukur, on the southern fringes of the city. 

 The Eastern Railway has decided to upgrade some express trains to the superfast category. The trains include the Howrah-Bolpur Shantiniketan Express, Howrah-Dhanbad Coalfield Express, Howrah-Asansol Agniveena Express, Howrah-Jammu Tawi Himgiri Express and the Howrah-Varansai Bibhuti Express.

 A bystander was injured after being hit by a car on BT Road, opposite Cossipore police station, on Thursday afternoon. Police said the car lost control, overturned and hit the bystander and a lamp post. The victim was admitted to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital. 

 Members of the Calcutta High Court Bar Association and Bar Library Club on Thursday mourned the death of Justice (retd) S.K. Hazari. The former judge died at a nursing home on Wednesday. 

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation will organise malaria and dengue awareness campaigns in educational institutions. Calcutta Institute of Engineering and Management, in Tollygunge, will host the first such event on Friday. Chief civic health officer Deb Dwaipayan Chattopadhyay said students will be shown audio-visual presentations on prevention of malaria and dengue. Doctors and entomologists will attend the programmes.

 The Indian Green Building Council, the body that has been promoting the concept of green building across the country, will launch its Calcutta chapter on Friday. The programme will be attended by state pollution control board chairman Sudip Bannerjee and the associate manager of LEED Customer Service of the US Green Building Council Sabrina Morelli, among others. 

 The state government has decided to enhance its annual salary grant to the Calcutta Municipal Corporation by Rs 20 crore, to Rs 260 crore. This follows municipal commissioner Alapan Bandyopadhyay submitting to the government the ?actual number? of employees on the civic body?s pay roll, officials said on Thursday. 

 A 45-year-old woman was injured after being hit by a car near the toll plaza on Vidyasagar Setu on Thursday. Police said the woman was taken to SSKM Hospital. The driver was detained and the vehicle impounded.

